title: 1982–83 DFB-Pokal Frauen
content: The Frauen DFB-Pokal 1982–83 was the 3rd season of the cup competition, Germany's second-most important title in women's football.[1] In the final which was held in Frankfurt on 8 May 1983 KBC Duisburg defeated FSV Frankfurt 3–0,[2] thus claiming their first national title.
